title: 'Will Hillary Clinton Get Prosecuted': Most-Googled Hillary Search During Democratic Debate
title_page: 'Will Hillary Clinton Get Prosecuted': Most-Googled Hillary Search During Democratic Debate | Breitbart
text:
“Will Hillary Clinton get prosecuted” was the most Googled search result for Clinton during Sunday night’s Democratic debate in South Carolina.
Research compiled by Google shows that “Will Hillary Clinton get prosecuted” led the way in Clinton-related searches when the debate ended, having already taken the top spot before 10:20 PM. The debate ran for two hours between 9 and 11 PM Eastern Time.
“What did Hillary Clinton do that was illegal” came in third.
By contrast, the top-trending question for Bernie Sanders was “Why is Bernie Sanders so popular?”
“Can Bernie Sanders win?” came in second.
Sanders also led Clinton in terms of Facebook engagement during the debate, and his home state of Vermont was the most-engaged state on Facebook.
